{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"What if an African girl\nfrom a traditional family"},{"time":4000,"text":"in a part of future Africa"},{"time":6160,"text":"is accepted into the finest\nuniversity in the galaxy,"},{"time":9920,"text":"planets away?"},{"time":12280,"text":"What if she decides to go?"},{"time":15360,"text":"This is an excerpt\nfrom my \"Binti\" novella trilogy:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20120,"text":"I powered up the transporter\nand said a silent prayer."},{"time":23600,"text":"I had no idea what I was going\nto do if it didn't work."},{"time":26880,"text":"My transporter was cheap,"},{"time":28320,"text":"so even a droplet of moisture\nor, more likely, a grain of sand,"},{"time":31920,"text":"would cause it to short."},{"time":33800,"text":"It was faulty, and most of the time\nI had to restart it over and over"},{"time":37080,"text":"before it worked."},{"time":38320,"text":"\"Please not now,\nplease not now,\" I thought."},{"time":41560,"text":"The transporter shivered in the sand\nand I held my breath."},{"time":45200,"text":"Tiny, flat and black as a prayer stone,"},{"time":47520,"text":"it buzzed softly and then\nslowly rose from the sand."},{"time":51760,"text":"Finally, it produced\nthe baggage-lifting force."},{"time":54280,"text":"I grinned."},{"time":55840,"text":"Now I could make it\nto the shuttle on time."},{"time":59360,"text":"I swiped otjize from my forehead\nwith my index finger and knelt down,"},{"time":63720,"text":"then I touched the finger to the sand,"},{"time":65600,"text":"grounding the sweet-smelling\nred clay into it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68080,"text":"\"Thank you,\" I whispered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71040,"text":"It was a half-mile walk\nalong the dark desert road."},{"time":74040,"text":"With the transporter working\nI would make it there on time."},{"time":78080,"text":"Straightening up,\nI paused and shut my eyes."},{"time":80840,"text":"Now, the weight of my entire life\nwas pressing on my shoulders."},{"time":84760,"text":"I was defying the most traditional\npart of myself for the first time"},{"time":88000,"text":"in my entire life."},{"time":89600,"text":"I was leaving in the dead of night,\nand they had no clue."},{"time":93760,"text":"My nine siblings, all older than me\nexcept for my younger sister and brother,"},{"time":97440,"text":"would never see this coming."},{"time":99480,"text":"My parents would never imagine\nI'd do such a thing in a million years."},{"time":103640,"text":"By the time they all realized\nwhat I'd done and where I was going,"},{"time":107440,"text":"I'd have left the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110840,"text":"In my absence, my parents\nwould growl to each other"},{"time":113560,"text":"that I was never\nto set foot in their home again."},{"time":116440,"text":"My four aunties and two uncles\nwho lived down the road"},{"time":119040,"text":"would shout and gossip amongst themselves"},{"time":121040,"text":"about how I had scandalized\nthe entire bloodline."},{"time":124360,"text":"I was going to be a pariah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127000,"text":"\"Go,\" I softly whispered\nto the transporter,"},{"time":129759,"text":"stamping my foot."},{"time":131600,"text":"The thin metal rings I wore\naround each ankle jingled noisily,"},{"time":134840,"text":"but I stamped my foot again."},{"time":137440,"text":"Once on, the transporter worked best\nwhen I didn't touch it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140800,"text":"\"Go,\" I said again,\nsweat forming on my brow."},{"time":144600,"text":"When nothing moved,"},{"time":145880,"text":"I chanced giving the two large suitcases\nsitting atop the force field a shove."},{"time":150520,"text":"They moved smoothly,\nand I breathed another sigh of relief."},{"time":153600,"text":"At least some luck was on my side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158360,"text":"So, in a distant future part of Africa,"},{"time":161800,"text":"Binti is a mathematical genius\nof the Himba ethnic group."},{"time":165600,"text":"She's been accepted\ninto a university on another planet,"},{"time":168320,"text":"and she's decided to go."},{"time":170760,"text":"Carrying the blood\nof her people in her veins,"},{"time":172960,"text":"adorned with the teachings,\nways, even the land on her very skin,"},{"time":177760,"text":"Binti leaves the earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180480,"text":"As the story progresses,\nshe becomes not other, but more."},{"time":184360,"text":"This idea of leaving but bringing\nand then becoming more"},{"time":187560,"text":"is at one of the hearts of Afrofuturism,"},{"time":190480,"text":"or you can simply call it\na different type of science fiction."},{"time":194920,"text":"I can best explain the difference between\nclassic science fiction and Afrofuturism"},{"time":199080,"text":"if I used the octopus analogy."},{"time":202680,"text":"Like humans,"},{"time":203920,"text":"octopuses are some of the most\nintelligent creatures on earth."},{"time":207120,"text":"However, octopus intelligence evolved\nfrom a different evolutionary line,"},{"time":212080,"text":"separate from that of human beings,"},{"time":214600,"text":"so the foundation is different."},{"time":217000,"text":"The same can be said about the foundations\nof various forms of science fiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222800,"text":"So much of science fiction speculates"},{"time":225480,"text":"about technologies,\nsocieties, social issues,"},{"time":228720,"text":"what's beyond our planet,\nwhat's within our planet."},{"time":231760,"text":"Science fiction is one of the greatest\nand most effective forms"},{"time":234760,"text":"of political writing."},{"time":236440,"text":"It's all about the question, \"What if?\""},{"time":239800,"text":"Still, not all science fiction\nhas the same ancestral bloodline,"},{"time":244760,"text":"that line being Western-rooted\nscience fiction,"},{"time":247760,"text":"which is mostly white and male."},{"time":250200,"text":"We're talking Isaac Asimov, Jules Verne,"},{"time":253720,"text":"H.G. Wells, George Orwell,\nRobert Heinlein, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258839,"text":"So what if a Nigerian-American\nwrote science fiction?"},{"time":263600,"text":"Growing up, I didn't\nread much science fiction."},{"time":266920,"text":"I couldn't relate to these stories"},{"time":268640,"text":"preoccupied with xenophobia,\ncolonization and seeing aliens as others."},{"time":274240,"text":"And I saw no reflection of anyone\nwho looked like me in those narratives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278840,"text":"In the \"Binti\" novella trilogy,"},{"time":280400,"text":"Binti leaves the planet\nto seek education from extraterrestrials."},{"time":284720,"text":"She goes out as she is,"},{"time":286480,"text":"looking the way she looks,"},{"time":288160,"text":"carrying her cultures,"},{"time":289800,"text":"being who she is."},{"time":292120,"text":"I was inspired to write this story"},{"time":293800,"text":"not because I was following\na line of classic space opera narratives,"},{"time":298000,"text":"but because of blood that runs deep,"},{"time":300360,"text":"family, cultural conflict"},{"time":303000,"text":"and the need to see an African girl\nleave the planet on her own terms."},{"time":308640,"text":"My science fiction\nhad different ancestors,"},{"time":311640,"text":"African ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314560,"text":"So I'm Nigerian-American."},{"time":316720,"text":"I was born to two\nNigerian immigrant parents"},{"time":319240,"text":"and raised in the United States,"},{"time":321400,"text":"one of the birthplaces\nof classic science fiction."},{"time":324120,"text":"However, it was my Nigerian heritage\nthat led me to write science fiction."},{"time":329440,"text":"Specifically I cite those family trips\nto Nigeria in the late '90s."},{"time":335040,"text":"I'd been taking trips back to Nigeria\nwith my family since I was very young."},{"time":339960,"text":"These early trips inspired me."},{"time":342560,"text":"Hence the first story that I ever\neven wrote took place in Nigeria."},{"time":346800,"text":"I wrote mainly magical realism and fantasy"},{"time":349720,"text":"inspired by my love of Igbo"},{"time":351320,"text":"and other West African traditional\ncosmologies and spiritualities."},{"time":356400,"text":"However, in the late '90s,"},{"time":359000,"text":"I started noticing\nthe role of technology in Nigeria:"},{"time":363240,"text":"cable TV and cell phones in the village,"},{"time":366120,"text":"419 scammers occupying the cybercafes,"},{"time":369920,"text":"the small generator connected\nto my cousin's desktop computer"},{"time":373360,"text":"because the power\nwas always going on and off."},{"time":376760,"text":"And my Americanness othered me enough"},{"time":379160,"text":"to be intrigued by these things\nthat most Nigerians saw as normal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384400,"text":"My intrigue eventually\ngave birth to stories."},{"time":388320,"text":"I started opening strange doors."},{"time":392480,"text":"What if aliens came to Lagos, Nigeria?"},{"time":398800,"text":"This is an excerpt\nfrom my novel, \"Lagoon.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":404320,"text":"Everybody saw it,"},{"time":406320,"text":"all over the world."},{"time":408760,"text":"That was a real introduction\nto the great mess happening in Lagos,"},{"time":412320,"text":"Nigeria, West Africa, Africa, here."},{"time":418360,"text":"Because so many people in Lagos\nhad portable, chargeable,"},{"time":421480,"text":"glowing, vibrating, chirping, tweeting,\ncommunicating, connected devices,"},{"time":425920,"text":"practically everything was recorded\nand posted online in some way,"},{"time":429640,"text":"somehow,"},{"time":431160,"text":"quickly."},{"time":433080,"text":"The modern human world\nis connected like a spider's web."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438040,"text":"The world was watching."},{"time":440200,"text":"It watched in fascinated horror"},{"time":442480,"text":"for information,"},{"time":444560,"text":"but mostly for entertainment."},{"time":447200,"text":"Footage of what was happening\ndominated every international news source,"},{"time":450760,"text":"video-sharing website, social network,\ncircle, pyramid and trapezoid."},{"time":455800,"text":"But the story goes deeper."},{"time":458080,"text":"It is in the mud,"},{"time":459840,"text":"the dirt,"},{"time":461400,"text":"the earth,"},{"time":463160,"text":"in the fond memory of the soily cosmos."},{"time":466560,"text":"It is in the always mingling\npast, present and future."},{"time":470560,"text":"It is in the water."},{"time":472640,"text":"It is in the powerful spirits\nand ancestors who dwelled in Lagos."},{"time":476560,"text":"It is in the hearts and minds\nof the people of Lagos."},{"time":480720,"text":"Change begets change."},{"time":483160,"text":"The alien Ayodele knew it."},{"time":485720,"text":"All her people know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489200,"text":"So, this is a voice of Udide,\nthe supreme spider artist,"},{"time":493080,"text":"who is older than dirt"},{"time":494440,"text":"and lives in the dirt\nbeneath the city of Lagos,"},{"time":497040,"text":"listening and commenting"},{"time":499000,"text":"and weaving the story\nof extraterrestrials coming to Lagos."},{"time":503120,"text":"In the end, the great spider\nwho was the size of a house"},{"time":506880,"text":"and responsible for weaving\nthe past, present and future"},{"time":509840,"text":"decides to come forth\nand be a part of the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513559,"text":"Like Udide, the spider artist,"},{"time":515960,"text":"African science fiction's blood runs deep"},{"time":519159,"text":"and it's old,"},{"time":520960,"text":"and it's ready to come forth,"},{"time":523240,"text":"and when it does,"},{"time":524840,"text":"imagine the new technologies, ideas\nand sociopolitical changes it'll inspire."},{"time":531520,"text":"For Africans, homegrown\nscience fiction can be a will to power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536840,"text":"What if?"},{"time":538520,"text":"It's a powerful question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540600,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541840,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}